public class RecurringEvent extends AbstractEvent
Represents a recurring event that generates multiple single event occurrences.

  • Constructor Details

    • RecurringEvent

      public RecurringEvent(String subject, LocalDateTime startDateTime, LocalDateTime endDateTime, String description, String location, boolean isPublic, Set<DayOfWeek> recurrenceDays, int occurrenceCount, LocalDate recurrenceEndDate) throws InvalidDateException
      Constructs a RecurringEvent with the specified parameters.
      Parameters:
      subject - the event subject
      startDateTime - the start date and time of the event series
      endDateTime - the end date and time for each occurrence; must be on the same day as startDateTime
      description - a description of the event
      location - the location of the event
      isPublic - true if the event is public, false otherwise
      recurrenceDays - the set of days on which the event recurs
      occurrenceCount - the number of occurrences; use -1 if not specified
      recurrenceEndDate - the end date of the recurrence series; may be null if occurrenceCount is specified
      Throws:
      InvalidDateException - throws exception for invalid date
